                    <span>Only about 20% of this book is about baseball.  If the author didn't have his own agenda, it could have been closer to 80 or 90%.    The best parts of the book are Appendix 1 (almost all SABR material) and the annotated bibliography.  A good idea squandered.</span>
                  
              
